    <!-- Chosen Palette: Brilliant Blues with a vibrant yellow accent (#0D47A1, #1976D2, #42A5F5, #90CAF9, #FFD600) -->
    <!-- Narrative Plan: The infographic tells a linear story to guide a potential customer from understanding a problem to seeing a solution. It starts with a bold hook, then clearly defines and differentiates "Business Retreats" from familiar concepts (Offsites/Workshops). Next, it showcases the concrete offerings and visualizes the tangible impact with data charts. The story concludes by outlining the simple engagement process and a clear call to action, building confidence and encouraging contact. This structure is designed to be persuasive and easy to follow in a single scroll. -->
    <!-- Visualization Choices: 
        - Data Point: Differentiation of Retreats vs. Offsites/Workshops -> Goal: Compare -> Visualization: Styled HTML/Tailwind grid -> Justification: Provides a clear, static side-by-side comparison which is highly readable in an infographic format. (Method: HTML/CSS, NO SVG).
        - Data Point: Core Service Offerings -> Goal: Organize/Inform -> Visualization: Icon-based cards using HTML/Tailwind and Unicode characters -> Justification: Segments services into digestible, visually distinct blocks. (Method: HTML/CSS, NO SVG).
        - Data Point: Focus of a Retreat -> Goal: Inform (Show Composition) -> Visualization: Donut Chart -> Justification: Immediately communicates that a retreat is a holistic mix of different elements (strategy, team, growth), not a single-focus event. (Library: Chart.js/Canvas, NO SVG).
        - Data Point: Long-term Impact Comparison -> Goal: Compare -> Visualization: Bar Chart -> Justification: Best choice to directly compare a key metric (long-term value) across the three event types, providing a strong quantitative argument. (Library: Chart.js/Canvas, NO SVG).
        - Data Point: Engagement Process -> Goal: Organize (Process Flow) -> Visualization: Numbered steps with connecting lines using HTML/Tailwind -> Justification: Simple, clear visualization of a linear process without complex graphics. (Method: HTML/CSS, NO SVG/Mermaid).
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
